userStories.description:
**Shared feature branch** — Part of the Epic Detail Page epic. All tickets share one branch.

## Goal
Create the `EpicLearnings` component that displays accumulated learnings from completed tickets in a collapsible panel.

## File to Create

### `src/components/epics/EpicLearnings.tsx`

**Props:**
```ts
interface LearningEntry {
  ticketId: string;
  ticketTitle: string;
  learnings: Array<{
    type: "pattern" | "anti-pattern" | "tool-usage" | "workflow";
    description: string;
    suggestedUpdate?: {
      file: string;
      section: string;
      content: string;
    };
  }>;
  appliedAt: string;
}

interface EpicLearningsProps {
  learnings: LearningEntry[];
}
```

**Features:**
- Collapsible section with ChevronDown/ChevronUp toggle (collapsed by default)
- Section header: "Learnings" with count badge
- Grouped by source ticket (ticketId/ticketTitle)
- Each learning shows:
  - Type badge with color: pattern (green), anti-pattern (red), tool-usage (blue), workflow (purple)
  - Description text
  - Optional suggested update info (file + section) in a subtle sub-line
- Empty state: "No learnings captured yet. Complete tickets in this epic to accumulate learnings."
- Use CSS variables for styling consistency

**Reference:** Learnings data structure from `src/lib/schema.ts` `WorkflowLearning` type and `core/learnings.ts`

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Collapsible panel toggles open/closed
- [ ] Learnings grouped by source ticket
- [ ] Type badges render with correct colors
- [ ] Suggested updates show file/section when present
- [ ] Empty state renders when no learnings
- [ ] `pnpm type-check` passes

## Branch Strategy
**All tickets in this epic work on the same branch:**  (branched from `feature/epic-b65163de-align-provider-setup-scripts-with-post-refactor-ar`). Do NOT create a new branch — commit directly to this existing branch so all changes can be tested together before merging to feature/epic-b65163de-align-provider-setup-scripts-with-post-refactor-ar
